OL,5,Ccourt
OL,7,FDistrict Judge Hirst was told the
OL,8,Fboy's mother was not present, having
OL,9,Fbooked a holiday in July and gone
OL,10,Fabroad.
OL,12,FShe thanked the boy's uncle for
OL,13,Faccompanying his nephew to court in
OL,14,Fhis mother's absence, but added: "One
OL,15,Fday before the hearing we find out the
OL,16,Fmum has gone on holiday and is not
OL,17,Fwith her son who played a greater part
OL,18,Fin the recent civil disorder than any
OL,19,Fadult or child I've seen coming
OL,20,Fthrough these courts. I'm frankly
OL,21,Fastonished.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/9
